SpeciesDescription: Legends say their touch can bridge the gap between realities,
While some believe Graplinth can freely navigate between dimensions,
They're known for their constant chirping,
Their chirping evolves into a more complex song, some believe it contains hidden messages or carries good luck.
Cactoro are surprisingly social creatures,
Cactrika are fierce protectors of their desert homes and will use their powerful arms and spined body to fend off any threats.
Despite their unassuming appearance,
Blobstrike are agile predators, using their strong arms to propel themselves through the water at surprising speeds and their tails to deliver powerful blows.
It has a small heart and brain. Its stomach comprises most of its body, with enzymes to dissolve anything.
It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.
The spores released from this Pokemon’s hands are highly poisonous, but when thoroughly dried, the spores can be used as stomach medicine.
Mushnub live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This Pokemon feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.
It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.
Snowti are playful creatures,
They are incredibly strong and resilient,
Ninjub are masters of stealth,
Their loyalty to their trainers deepens with evolution, and they are willing to take any blow meant for their companions.
They are surprisingly fast for their size and fiercely defend their territory from any perceived threats.
Grorc are the soldiers of orc communities,
Their swings carry the force of a battering ram, and their battle cry can strike fear into the hearts of even the most courageous opponents.
A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.
It slowly flies in a circular pattern, all the while keeping a sharp lookout for prey.
Despite their perpetually tearful appearance,
Whistleweep are playful creatures,
Alpalin are incredibly elusive and rarely interact with other Pokemon or humans.
Combalpa are the undisputed rulers of the skies,
Been are incredibly social creatures,
They work alongside Been in their hives, collecting pollen and defending their home from predators.
Dimp are drawn to negative emotions,
Dreamon are masters of illusion,
Chik are known for their playful personalities and their tendency to peck at anything that catches their interest.
Chark retains the playful personality of its pre-evolved form but also develops a fierce protectiveness over its territory and loved ones.
Chragon are powerful and majestic creatures,
Gosty are known for their love of pranks,
While not inherently malicious, Gostaunt can be mischievous and may drain a bit more energy than intended, leaving their victims feeling weak and disoriented.
lub attach themselves to unsuspecting creatures using their powerful suckers,
Plonster are not only parasitic but also feed on the negative emotions of others, growing stronger with despair and misery.
Unlike most bats, Gapark use echolocation through vibrations in the ground rather than sound waves.
Kingapark are the undisputed rulers of the caves they inhabit,
Their purrs emit psychic waves that can calm emotions or even induce headaches in those they dislike.
Their barks sound like thunderclaps.
They love hiding decorated eggs (real or energy-based) for others to find.
Bonkster are powerful fighters with ice-covered fur and horns. They fiercely defend their territory.
They breathe fire hotter than molten lava.
They can generate powerful electric shocks while swimming.
They throw toxic berries at their opponents and hide amongst boulders.
Each Ungaring paints its own individual pattern, and it will paint that same pattern over and over again throughout its life.
They inhabit abandoned buildings and feed off negative emotions.
If this Pokemon senses a strong emotion, it will run away as fast as it can. It prefers areas without people.
